ActCustoms Tariff
SubjectCUKTCA Rules of Origin for Casual Goods Regulations
PrecisCUKTCA RULES OF ORIGIN FOR CASUAL GOODS REGULATIONS in order to establish that non-commercial goods acquired in the U.K. and certain associated territories, that are either marked as made in a country eligible to CUKTCA tariff treatment or not marked to the contrary, are considered originating and therefore entitled to the relevant CUKTCA tariff preferences upon their importation to Canada.
